text: Kurshaki () is a rural locality (a village) in Chuvash-Kubovsky Selsoviet, Iglinsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 219 as of 2010. There are 3 streets. == Geography == It is located 10 km from Iglino, 1.5 km from Chuvash-Kubovo. == References == Category:Rural localities in Iglinsky District
title: Kurshaki
